# CI-only tooling for the dependency-audit job in .github/workflows/test.yml
# (Story 10.40 / SEC-13, SEC-14, triple-threat review follow-up). pip-audit
# is the scanner that audits requirements.lock / requirements-dev.lock — kept
# in its own lockfile rather than folded into requirements-dev.lock because
# it's CI-only tooling, not a project dev dependency. Pinned + hash-verified
# like every other install this story wires into CI, so the auditor itself
# can't be a floating, unverified supply-chain risk.
pip-audit>=2.10,<3
